race.comment: One of the toughest races of the day, which might come up at the right time for ZIGGY STARCRAFT (1) who is yet to find the frame in two runs since resuming from a spell but gets to 1600m for the first time in his career. The inside gate and Will Gordon to ride are just added bonuses. TORBELO (5) made progress last time out, finishing 2.5 lengths from the winner in third at the end of 2200m at Ararat. Finds a suitable race and can find the winner's circle. BRUZANI (3) resumed over 1400m last time out and turned in a solid effort to finish second at Mt Gambier. Won't be bothered by this longer journey and looks one of the main contenders. THE DAILY PLANET (4) hasn't won in over a year and has a horror gate, but has raced consistently this prep and looks ready for the mile. JAZ TYCOON (2) hasn't won for a long time but wasn't beaten far at the first run for the new stable and draws to get his chance.
